  "prompt": "Can I get into the CSE in VIT Chennai at 70+ marks?",
  "response": "Admission to the Computer Science and Engineering (CSE) program at VIT Chennai typically depends on your VITEEE (VIT Engineering Entrance Examination) score, along with other factors such as your overall rank and the cutoff scores for that particular year.\n\nWhile the exact cutoff can vary from year to year based on several factors (including the number of applicants, difficulty of the exam, and more), a score of 70+ marks in VITEEE might be on the lower side for the CSE branch, as it is one of the more sought-after programs and often has higher cutoffs.\n\nTo get a more accurate assessment, you would want to check:\n\n1. The previous year's cutoff scores for the CSE program at VIT Chennai.\n2. The overall competition and the number of candidates applying.\n\nI suggest checking the official VIT website or contacting their admissions office for the most updated and precise information regarding admission probabilities with your scores.",
